# PueueWrapper Project Structure Guide

This project follows a structured layout for better organization:

## Core Directories

- **Source Code**: All main code is located in [src/](mdc:src/) directory
- **Documentation**: All documentation files are placed in [docs/](mdc:docs/) directory  
- **Examples**: Quick tests and usage examples are stored in [examples/](mdc:examples/) directory

## Main Entry Points

- **Models**: [src/pueue_wrapper/models/](mdc:src/pueue_wrapper/models/) - Pydantic data models
- **Package Init**: [src/pueue_wrapper/__init__.py](mdc:src/pueue_wrapper/__init__.py) - Package exports

Interfaces:

- **Async Wrapper**: [src/pueue_wrapper/pueue_wrapper.py](mdc:src/pueue_wrapper/pueue_wrapper.py) - Main async implementation
- **Sync Wrapper**: [src/pueue_wrapper/pueue_sync_wrapper.py](mdc:src/pueue_wrapper/pueue_sync_wrapper.py) - Synchronous wrapper
- **API**: [api.py](mdc:api.py) - Host the wrapper with FastAPI

NOTE: when you update a new interface, you should update all interface as well. Including Async Wrapper, Sync Wrapper, and API

## Package Management

- Uses **UV** as the package manager
- Dependencies are defined in [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml)
- Lock file is [uv.lock](mdc:uv.lock)

## Examples and Testing

- Status examples: [examples/example_status.py](mdc:examples/example_status.py)
- Usage examples: [examples/example_usage.py](mdc:examples/example_usage.py)
